---
name: external-review
description: "Run an external review tool and write findings to QA.md."
---

Run an external code review tool to review all changes on the current branch.

## Instructions

1. Verify the external review tool is available (user-supplied command, or Code Rabbit CLI default).
2. Run the review tool against all changes on the current branch compared to `<%= mainBranch %>`.
3. Format the findings into `QA.md` with severity tags:
   - `[critical]` — must fix before merge
   - `[warning]` — should fix, may defer with justification
   - `[suggestion]` — nice to have, can skip
4. Print a summary: total findings by severity, top 3 most important issues.

## Command selection

Users may pass a terminal command after the slash command to override the default tool.
Example: `/external-review cursor-bugbot review --base <%= mainBranch %>`

When a terminal command is supplied, the agent must run exactly that command and parse its
output into `QA.md`. Do not alter or substitute the supplied command.

Before executing any user-supplied command, verify it does not contain shell metacharacters
that suggest command substitution, piping to a shell, or destructive operations
(e.g. `$(...)`, backtick substitution, `| sh`, `| bash`, `rm -rf`, `>`,
`&&` chained destructive ops). If the command looks suspicious, halt and ask the user
to confirm before proceeding; do NOT silently substitute a different tool.

When no terminal command is supplied, the default tool is the **Code Rabbit CLI**
(`coderabbit review` or vendor-current equivalent — verify availability via
`coderabbit --version`).

If Code Rabbit CLI is not installed, halt and instruct the user to either install it or
re-invoke with an explicit command argument. Do NOT silently substitute another tool.

## Cross-model requirement

The external review tool **must** run on a different model family than the implementer and
code-reviewer used for the diff. Family parity between the writer and the final reviewer is
forbidden. See §1.7 of the project PRD for the full model-routing rationale.

## Output

Write findings to `QA.md` in the repository root with this format:

```markdown
# QA Review

_Generated by external review tool on YYYY-MM-DD_

> **Note**: These findings are automated and may be inaccurate. Always verify before applying fixes.

## Findings

- [ ] [severity] **Title** — Description. File: `path/to/file.ts:line`
```

